\",\"topic\":\"1.4 Quranic instructions to reveal the study of life\",\"marks\":1,\"text\":\"The Quran mentions animals creeping on their bellies as:\",\"options\":[\"Humans and insects\",\"Fishes and mammals\",\"Birds and amphibians\",\"Snakes and reptiles\"],\"answer\":\"Snakes and reptiles\",\"source\":\"exercise\",\"medium\":\"ENGLISH MEDIUM\",\"class\":\"9th\",\"subject\":\"Biology\",\"created_at\":\"2025-03-29 17:42:17\"},{\"id\":\"48\",\"type\":\"mcqs\",\"chapter\":\"Chapter 1: The Science of Biology\",\"topic\":\"1.5 Science as collaborative field\",\"marks\":1,\"text\":\"The Human Genome Project was completed in:\",\"options\":[\"2000\",\"2015\",\"2010\",\"2003\"],\"answer\":\"2003\",\"source\":\"exercise\",\"medium\":\"ENGLISH MEDIUM\",\"class\":\"9th\",\"subject\":\"Biology\",\"created_at\":\"2025-03-29 17:42:17\"},{\"id\":\"51\",\"type\":\"mcqs\",\"chapter\":\"Chapter 1: The Science of Biology\",\"topic\":\"1.5 Science as collaborative field\",\"marks\":1,\"text\":\"Robotics and AI are interdisciplinary fields that involve:\",\"options\":[\"Biology and economics\",\"Mathematics and neuroscience\",\"Sociology and geology\",\"Atmospheric science and physics\"],\"answer\":\"Mathematics and neuroscience\",\"source\":\"exercise\",\"medium\":\"ENGLISH MEDIUM\",\"class\":\"9th\",\"subject\":\"Biology\",\"created_at\":\"2025-03-29 17:42:17\"},{\"id\":\"52\",\"type\":\"mcqs\",\"chapter\":\"Chapter 1: The Science of Biology\",\"topic\":\"1.5 Science as collaborative field\",\"marks\":1,\"text\":\"Space exploration involves collaboration in fields such as:\",\"options\":[\"Astrophysics, biology, and medicine\",\"Sociology, informatics, and mathematics\",\"Psychology and economics\",\"Engineering and social sciences\"],\"answer\":\"Astrophysics, biology, and medicine\",\"source\":\"exercise\",\"medium\":\"ENGLISH MEDIUM\",\"class\":\"9th\",\"subject\":\"Biology\",\"created_at\":\"2025-03-29 17:42:17\"},{\"id\":\"57\",\"type\":\"mcqs\",\"chapter\":\"Chapter 1: The Science of Biology\",\"topic\":\"1.6 Scientific method\",\"marks\":1,\"text\":\"What is the first step in the scientific method?\",\"options\":[\"Hypothesis\",\"Observation\",\"Recognition of a problem\",\"Experimentation\"],\"answer\":\"Observation\",\"source\":\"exercise\",\"medium\":\"ENGLISH MEDIUM\",\"class\":\"9th\",\"subject\":\"Biology\",\"created_at\":\"2025-03-29 17:42:17\"},{\"id\":\"59\",\"type\":\"mcqs\",\"chapter\":\"Chapter 1: The Science of Biology\",\"topic\":\"1.6 Scientific method\",\"marks\":1,\"text\":\"What type of observations involve characteristics that can be measured with numbers?\",\"options\":[\"Quantitative\",\"Qualitative\",\"Descriptive\",\"Experimental\"],\"answer\":\"Quantitative\",\"source\":\"exercise\",\"medium\":\"ENGLISH MEDIUM\",\"class\":\"9th\",\"subject\":\"Biology\",\"created_at\":\"2025-03-29 17:42:17\"},{\"id\":\"6\",\"type\":\"mcqs\",\"chapter\":\"Chapter 1: The Science of Biology\",\"topic\":\"1.1 Biology and its branches\",\"marks\":1,\"text\":\"Microorganisms studied in Microbiology include:\",\"options\":[\"Amphibians and reptiles\",\"Mammals and birds\",\"Trees and shrubs\",\"Bacteria and microscopic fungi\"],\"answer\":\"Bacteria and microscopic fungi\",\"source\":\"exercise\",\"medium\":\"ENGLISH MEDIUM\",\"class\":\"9th\",\"subject\":\"Biology\",\"created_at\":\"2025-03-29 17:42:17\"},{\"id\":\"61\",\"type\":\"mcqs\",\"chapter\":\"Chapter 1: The Science of Biology\",\"topic\":\"1.6 Scientific method\",\"marks\":1,\"text\":\"The control group in an experiment is used for:\",\"options\":[\"Testing the hypothesis\",\"Comparing results\",\"Developing new hypotheses\",\"Making observations\"],\"answer\":\"Comparing results\",\"source\":\"exercise\",\"medium\":\"ENGLISH MEDIUM\",\"class\":\"9th\",\"subject\":\"Biology\",\"created_at\":\"2025-03-29 17:42:17\"},{\"id\":\"63\",\"type\":\"mcqs\",\"chapter\":\"Chapter 1: The Science of Biology\",\"topic\":\"1.6 Scientific method\",\"marks\":1,\"text\":\"In an experiment to test the necessity of carbon dioxide for photosynthesis, the group that will not receive carbon dioxide is:\",\"options\":[\"Experimental group\",\"Control group\",\"Both groups\",\"Neither group\"],\"answer\":\"Experimental group\",\"source\":\"exercise\",\"medium\":\"ENGLISH MEDIUM\",\"class\":\"9th\",\"subject\":\"Biology\",\"created_at\":\"2025-03-29 17:42:17\"},{\"id\":\"64\",\"type\":\"mcqs\",\"chapter\":\"Chapter 1: The Science of Biology\",\"topic\":\"1.6 Scientific method\",\"marks\":1,\"text\":\"In an experiment on plant growth, a scientist adds iron to the soil. If the hypothesis is true, what will happen to the plant growth?\",\"options\":[\"The plant will grow slower\",\"The plant will grow taller and healthier\",\"The plant will stop growing\",\"The plant will die\"],\"answer\":\"The plant will grow taller and healthier\",\"source\":\"exercise\",\"medium\":\"ENGLISH MEDIUM\",\"class\":\"9th\",\"subject\":\"Biology\",\"created_at\":\"2025-03-29 17:42:17\"}]}', 'DELETED', '2025-03-31 18:49:17', '2025-06-23 09:02:50', NULL);
